message.content: Most women in Seychelles have a generally accepting attitude towards divorce. They view it as a viable option to end an unhappy or abusive marriage and believe that individuals have the right to seek happiness and fulfillment in their lives. Women in Seychelles understand that divorce can be a difficult and emotionally challenging process, but they prioritize personal well-being and the pursuit of a better future. They also recognize the importance of legal and financial rights for women during and after divorce, advocating for fair settlements and support systems. Overall, women in Seychelles perceive divorce as a means to escape unhappy marriages and embrace personal growth and independence.
